// WavTrack Footer Integration Rules
// This file provides guidance for integrating the Footer component into the WavTrack app

// Footer Component Integration
// The Footer component is already integrated into the BaseLayout component
// It includes:
// - Social media links with Framer Motion animations
// - Feedback button
// - Copyright information
// - Scroll-to-top button that appears when scrolling down 100px

// Layout Structure
// The app uses a flex-col min-h-screen layout structure in BaseLayout.tsx
// This ensures the footer is positioned at the bottom of the page
// The main content area uses flex-1 to take up available space

// Responsive Design
// The Footer is responsive with appropriate padding and spacing
// Social icons scale on hover with smooth animations
// The scroll-to-top button is positioned at the bottom right

// Animation Guidelines
// Use Framer Motion for animations
// Apply consistent animation durations (0.2s for most transitions)
// Use scale animations for interactive elements (1.1 on hover, 0.95 on tap)

// Best Practices
// - Keep the Footer component lightweight to avoid performance issues
// - Ensure the scroll-to-top button doesn't overlap with other UI elements
// - Maintain consistent spacing between Footer sections
// - Use semantic HTML elements for accessibility
// - Ensure all interactive elements have appropriate hover/focus states

// Optional Enhancements
// - Consider adding a "Back to Top" text label for better accessibility
// - Add more social media links as needed
// - Consider adding a newsletter signup form
// - Add links to Privacy Policy, Terms of Service, etc.

// Heading Level Hierarchy Rules
// This file provides guidance for maintaining proper heading level hierarchy

// Heading Level Rules
// - Heading levels should only increase by one level at a time
// - Example: h1 -> h2 -> h3 (correct)
// - Example: h1 -> h3 (incorrect, missing h2)
// - Example: h2 -> h4 (incorrect, missing h3)

// Implementation Guidelines
// - Use the Typography component for all headings
// - Available heading variants: h1, h2, h3, h4
// - Each heading level should be semantically meaningful
// - Avoid skipping heading levels for visual styling
// - Use CSS classes for visual styling instead of heading levels

// Best Practices
// - Start with h1 for the main page title
// - Use h2 for major sections
// - Use h3 for subsections
// - Use h4 for minor sections
// - Use appropriate text styling classes for visual hierarchy
// - Maintain consistent heading structure across pages

// Example Usage
// <Typography variant="h1">Page Title</Typography>
// <Typography variant="h2">Major Section</Typography>
// <Typography variant="h3">Subsection</Typography>
// <Typography variant="h4">Minor Section</Typography>

// Visual Styling
// - Use text-fluid-* classes for responsive font sizes
// - Use font-* classes for font weights
// - Use tracking-* classes for letter spacing
// - Use mb-* classes for margin bottom
// - Use text-* classes for text colors

// Accessibility
// - Proper heading hierarchy improves screen reader navigation
// - Each page should have exactly one h1
// - Headings should be used for structure, not styling
// - Use appropriate ARIA labels when needed 